      <lg xml:id="TolE0110">
<l>niṟutta colluṅ kuṟittuvaru kiḷaviyu</l>
<l>maṭaiyoṭu tōṉṟiṉum puṇarnilaik kuriya</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>And they,</l>
<l>according to what they say,</l>
<l>are : one sound changing into another,<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">mey piṟitālal ;</foreign> assimilation, e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">poṉ + kuṭam &gt; poṟkuṭam.</foreign></note></l>
<l>addition,<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">mikutal,</foreign> sometimes rendered as ' insertion ', e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">yāṉai-k-kōṭu.</foreign></note> and loss.<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">kuṉṟal,</foreign> elision, e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">maram + ēr &gt; mara-v-ēr.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
